{
  "texts": [
    "We choose r to be a fraction of each layer's total dimensionality n, to achieve a consistent compression rate.",
    "Other works such as (Zhao et al., 2024) chose the same r for all compressed layers, which we think reduces potential compression gains.",
    "In Section 4 we experiment with ratios 1/2, 1/4, 1/8.",
    "Using this low-rank projection P, the gradients with respect to the weights and the input are calculated as follows:",
    "Our approach maintains the full forward pass, as well as the gradients with respect to the input."
  ]
